reviews.name: Adam Ukail
reviews.text: Call last week 7/8/25.nk buat apportionment.tp staff kata x perlu.next week dtg hari khamis 14/8/25 .walk in jam 2.sebab hari tu tiada appointment saraf..tiba harinya..Jam 2.45 sampai klinik..staff inform..da penuh.ada appointment lain..kite suruh dtg ham 2.00..kene sharp..klu tidak klinik da penuh appointment.tp di hall klinik wanty itu tiada org menunggu.bazir masa.bazir duit minyak.terus tolak.bukan kene tunggu.ikut turn..terus tolak mentah2.sakit hati betul..service teruk.
reviews.textTranslated: Called last week 7/8/25. Wanted to do an apportionment. But the staff said it wasn't necessary. Next week came on Thursday 14/8/25. Walk in at 2. Because there was no appointment that day.. The day arrived.. Arrived at the clinic at 2.45.. Staff informed.. It was full. There was another appointment.. We told them to come at 2.00.. It was sharp.. If not, the clinic was full for an appointment. But in the hall of the Wanty clinic there was no one waiting. Waste of time. Waste of money for fuel. Keep rejecting. Don't wait. Take the turn. Keep rejecting. Really hurt.. Bad service.
reviews.responseFromOwnerText:
Maaf atas pengalaman yang dilalui. Seperti yang pihak puan tulis, kami beri appointment pukul 2, tetapi puan datang 45 minit lewat daripada masa yang kami beri.

Kami mohon pihak puan memahami, yang kami ada appointment seterusnya pada pukul 3 ptg, dan proses pendaftaran, pembersihan kerusi, semua ambil paling kurang 5-10 minit. Dr juga perlukan masa secukupnya untuk buat pemeriksaan, 

Kalau kami terima puan, nanti kami akan mengambil hak masa pesakit lain. Jadi amatlah tidak adil untuk kami dahulukan puan tetapi abaikan masa pesakit lain.

Mohon jasa baik pihak puan memahami dan kalau boleh untuk datang tepat pada waktunya. 

Kami mohon maaf atas pengalaman pihak puan.

reviews.name: Siti Aishah
reviews.text: Kakak saya pergi ke klinik semalam , sehari sebelum pergi dia telah menelefon pihak klinik untuk book appointment . Tetapi pihak klinik inform tidak perlu appointment dan boleh walk in sahaja . Hari yang kakak saya pergi ke klinik . Dia menyerahkan ic di kaunter , akan tetapi staff di kaunter sangat tidak mesra , tidak menyapa pelanggan dengan baik , hanya duduk dan berkata yang klinik dah penuh dan tidak menerima pesakit sedangkan mereka inform tidak perlu appointment . Ini bukan sahaja menyusahkan kakak saya akan tetapi servis yang diberikan juga tidak bagus .
reviews.textTranslated: My sister went to the clinic yesterday, the day before she went she called the clinic to book an appointment. But the clinic informed her that an appointment was not required and that she could just walk in. The day my sister went to the clinic. She handed over her IC at the counter, but the staff at the counter were very unfriendly, did not greet customers properly, just sat and said that the clinic was full and did not accept patients even though they informed her that an appointment was not required. This not only inconvenienced my sister but the service provided was also not good.
reviews.responseFromOwnerText:
Hai cik, maaf atas pengalaman pihak kakak cik.

Klinik Faizal adalah klinik pertama di Masjid Tanah, dan semua warga Masjid Tanah tahu akan proses kami, iaitu first come first serve.

Klinik kami banyak merawat warga emas, kebanyakan mereka memang lebih selesa dgn proses first come first serve.

Untuk dapatkan rawatan, semua akan beratur dari awal klinik buka 

Maaf jika pihak cik tidak berapa familiar dgn proses klinik kami.

questionsAndAnswers.question:
(Translated by Google) How much does it cost to get braces?

(Original)
Berapa harga mau buat braces ?

answers.answer:
(Translated by Google) To make braces, you have to go to Luyang Dental Clinic to ask for a referral letter for braces first. Requirements must be under 18 years of age. After that, you will be referred to the orthodontic specialist clinic at HQE2. There people will check, xray, which needs to be removed. If it's urgent, you can continue doing it. But if the case is not urgent, it will be on the waiting list (I was on the waiting list for 3 years). When I make braces in 2022, the total price is RM1250.

(Original)
Untuk buat braces kena datang clinic gigi luyang untuk minta referral letter untuk braces dulu. Syarat mesti bawah umur 18 tahun. Lepas tu, akan kena refer to klinik pakar ortodontik di HQE2. Di sana dorang akan check, xray, yang mana perlu cabut. Kalau urgent, boleh buat terus. Tapi kalau kes tidak urgent akan berada di waiting list (Saya berada di waiting list selama 3 tahun) Masa saya buat braces tahun 2022, harga RM1250 total.

reviews.text:
I recently visited this dental clinic and unfortunately had a poor experience with the receptionist. From the moment I walked in, she seemed uninterested and dismissive. I tried to ask a few questions about my appointment, but her responses were curt and unhelpful, making me feel like I was an inconvenience rather than a valued patient. When I needed to clarify the details of the session, she was visibly irritated and provided no assistance in resolving my concerns.

This attitude was surprising, especially at a healthcare facility where patient care and comfort should be priorities. While I understand that clinics can be busy, a little professionalism and courtesy go a long way in making patients feel welcome. I hope the clinic addresses this issue to ensure a better experience for future patients.

reviews.name: Sarah Njw
reviews.text:
Buat braces 11/21 buka bulan 5/25.
My previous Dr. N kata boleh buka dalam setahun je. Tapi on my third braces review dia pasang braces (powerchain) tanpa besi kat bawah. Semua gigi bawah bergerak dan gusi bengkak. Bayangkan dari kata setahun jadi 3-4 tahun tanpa perubahan. Orang yg pakai kendian pun dah cabut. Lepastu supposedly saya dpt 11% off utk braces sbb layan live FB HQ diorang sebelum tu tp tak tahu la potong ke tak.

Kalau braces tercabut RM30/each
Kalau hilang RM50/each
Ni kalau nak cari klinik ada je yg tak minta bayar!

Awal2 dah habis bayar. Selebihnya datang sbb braces tercabut. Bayangkan setiap kali review ada 1/2 yg tercabut selama setahun lebih dah habis bayar.

Kawan saya pun buat kat KPS tp branch lain. Lawo dah gigi dia, cabut dah. Paling penting within setahun je?

Aku yang 3 tahun, tak settle2, yg dapat gigi goyang, masih jarak seperti kali pertama. Duit habis 7k gak? Ingatkan banyak branch kerja pun okay la. Sedih.

I hope my latest Dr in charge, Dr Anita tak kena marah la sbb bukan salah dia. Dr sebelum ni dah buat salah suh aku bayar RM150 utk satu gigi sbb nak buat laser pastu aku taknak lagi terus chawwww. MashaAllah sedihhhhhh duit habis hasil takde.
reviews.textTranslated:
Get braces 11/21 open 5/25.
My previous Dr. N said it can be removed within a year. But on my third braces review he put braces (powerchain) without metal at the bottom. All the lower teeth are moving and the gums are swollen. Imagine from saying a year to 3-4 years without any change. The person who wore the kendian has also had them removed. Then supposedly I got 11% off for braces because I watched their FB HQ live before but I don't know if they cut it or not.

If the braces are removed RM30/each
If they are lost RM50/each
If you want to find a clinic, there are only those who don't ask to pay!

I paid in advance. The rest came because the braces were removed. Imagine every review, 1/2 of them were removed for over a year and have already paid.

My friend also had it done at KPS but in another branch. They already had their teeth removed, they removed them. Most importantly, within a year?

I'm the one who's been there for 3 years, not settled, who got a loose tooth, still the same distance as the first time. The money is gone for 7k? Remember that many branches work okay too. Sad.

I hope my latest Dr in charge, Dr Anita, doesn't get angry because it's not her fault. The previous Dr made a mistake and I paid RM150 for one tooth because I wanted to do laser and then I don't want it anymore, so I'm sorry. MashaAllah, sadhhhhhh, the money is gone and there's no result.
reviews.responseFromOwnerText:
Pertama kali terima kasih Cik Najwa atas review yang diberikan. Kami faham dengan jelas atas kekecewaan Cik dengan pengalaman Dr braces yang menguruskan pada awal waktu Cik memakai braces.
Untuk pengetahuan Cik kami sentiasa cuba memberikan pengalaman rawatan yang berkualiti dan terbaik untuk pesakit kami. 
Dr.N yang cik maklumkan tidak lagi bertugas dengan klinik kami. Cik boleh teruskan rawatan dengan Dr. Anila yang professional dan berpengalaman. 
Segala aduan berkenaan dengan rawatan Cik boleh direct maklumkan kepada pihak Customer Service kami.

reviews.name: Quan Ze A
reviews.text:
I recently came from Melbourne to KK for just one night solely for dental work, including implants with Dr. Alex ‚Äî and I couldn‚Äôt be happier with the experience!

Everything was planned out before I arrived, which made the whole process really smooth and stress-free, especially since I was on an extremely tight schedule. Dr. Alex made it all happen within that short time, which was incredible. He is incredibly patient, knowledgeable, and takes the time to explain everything clearly ‚Äî I felt really well cared for from start to finish.

Big thanks to his lovely team as well ‚Äî everyone from the front desk to the assistants was so warm and welcoming, which made all the difference.

Also a special shoutout to Dr. Joanne for painting a few temporary teeth on my clear aligners so I could still smile confidently while waiting for my crowns. Such a thoughtful touch!

Highly recommend this clinic to anyone looking for professional, caring, and efficient dental care. Totally worth the trip!
reviews.responseFromOwnerText:
Dear Quan Ze,

Thank you for flying all the way from Melbourne and trusting us with your teeth. We are so happy to hear of your positive experience. Your kind feedback is sincerely appreciated. We look forward to seeing you again on your next trip back from Melbourne. In the meantime, do take care and stay safe! 

Regards, 
The Team @ Dr Alex Lo Dental Centre

reviews.name: Judd Harris
reviews.text: I recently visited Dr Alex Lo Dental Centre and had an exceptional experience. From the moment I walked in, the staff was welcoming and professional, making the check-in process smooth and easy. Dr. Joanne took the time to thoroughly explain my treatment options, I felt confident and comfortable knowing I was in good hands. The clinic itself is very clean, modern and calming, which made my visit feel more comfortable. I was also impressed with the clear aftercare instructions I received. Overall, my experience at Dr Alex Lo Dental Centre was excellent, and I would highly recommend them to anyone looking for high-quality dental care!
reviews.responseFromOwnerText:
Dear Judd, thank you for your visit and for taking the time to leave us a review. We do sincerely appreciate and value your feedback. We are so happy to hear that you had a positive experience at our clinic. We look forward to your next visit with us and wish you safe travels and good health till then. 

Regards,
The Team @ Dr Alex Lo Dental Centre

reviews.responseFromOwnerText:

reviews.name: Simple Lean
reviews.text:
I once trusted Alex Lo completely‚Äîhaving been his patient from childhood through adulthood‚Äîbut my recent experiences have left me profoundly disappointed. It seems that his focus has shifted from patient care to profit. I now believe he is frequently shuttling between Australia and KK, obsessing over converting Malaysian Ringgit to Australian Dollars, which suggests that financial gain has overtaken his commitment to ethical treatment. Please do not compared aussie dollar to RM and thinking is so cheap in KK. Our cost of living is different!

During my most recent visit, he performed dental procedures without offering a proper explanation and even removed teeth without my informed consent. This breach of trust, after nearly 20 years of care, is not only disheartening but also unacceptable. There are many other capable and ethical dentists in KK who prioritize patients over profit, and I can no longer recommend his services.

Furthermore, I ask that no response to my review claim a lack of patient records or insist that I come to the clinic to ‚Äúwork it out.‚Äù This feedback comes purely from a long-term patient and is not from a competitor. We are simply your patients, and we expect accountability for the care we receive.
reviews.responseFromOwnerText:
Dear sir/madam 'Simple Lean',

We do apologise that you had a negative experience on your last dental visit with us. Our team at Dr Alex Lo Dental Centre strive to provide ethical, scientific research based and the highest level of dental care to all patients. Unfortunately, after following up with our team members, we are unable to identify this incident. We take your feedback very seriously and would like to follow up with you. If you could kindly reach out and contact us on +6016 830 1215 to provide us with you name and date of your appointment, so that we can investigate this matter further. If you could kindly ask to speak to Dr Joanne directly to ensure that there are no further miscommunications. Please also rest assure that while Dr Alex does commute between Australia and Kota Kinabalu, he continues to attend to his patients concerns and needs and will attend to your review personally. Thanking you in advance and we look forward to hearing from you soon.

Kind regards,
The Team @ Dr Alex Lo¬†Dental¬†Centre

Husband sy dtg sbb sakit gg hujg yg tumbuh tu sgt sakit smpai xdpt tidur. Buat appointment mysejahtera full sampai tiada tarikh yg available. So kita dtg walk-in. Staff lelaki tu cakap 'kami full ni, kami utamakan yg ada appt, kami cuma layan kes trauma dan emergency sahaja', lps tu ramai la yg dtg dan terus pulang xdpt rawatan. Ada yg marah2 lagi sbb anaknya xdpt rawatan. Husband sy, staff tu cakap kalau mahu masuk juga kena tunggu lama la sbb ramai tu tengah menunggu. Sy ckp dgn suami masuk saja. End up dalam tu tidak ramai pun.  Tidak crowded mcm yg diwar2kan staff lelaki tu. X smpai 30 minit husband dah siap rawatan, thank you doc but please manage the staff. Kesian la yg dtg tak dapat rawatan tu padahal tak ramai pun pt. Buktinya rawatan tak lama pun. Staff lelaki tua tu layan org2 tua pun tak ramah ya.
reviews.textTranslated: Kudos to Doc. Doc here is very good and friendly, tiptop environment. The downside is from the nurses, especially the old man who takes care of the outside. The way they handle the pt seems to not want to accept patients. My husband came because he was sick with a growing gg hujg so much that he couldn't sleep. Made an appointment mysejahtera was full until there were no available dates. So we came walk-in. The male staff said 'we are full, we prioritize those with an appt, we only handle trauma and emergency cases', then many people came and went straight home without getting treatment. Some were even angry because their children couldn't get treatment. My husband, the staff said that if you want to go in, you have to wait a long time because there were many people waiting. I talked to my husband and just went in. Ended up there weren't many people inside. Not crowded like the male staff had told me. In 30 minutes my husband was done with the treatment, thank you doc ‚Äã‚Äãbut please manage the staff. It's a shame those who came couldn't get the treatment even though there weren't many people. The proof is that the treatment didn't last long. The old male staff didn't even treat the elderly people kindly.

reviews.name: tay phoebe
reviews.text:
Our entire family visited this doctor after my daughter tested positive for Influenza A at a pediatric clinic two nights earlier, as we were all showing similar symptoms. Upon arrival, I informed the doctor about my daughter's Influenza A diagnosis and expressed concern that we might have contracted the same virus. However, the doctor dismissed this and insisted that we all had bacterial infections based on his observations. He also mentioned that the clinic did not have an Influenza test kit and proceeded to prescribe antibiotics for all of us.
Unfortunately, this incorrect treatment (antibiotics instead of antivirals for Influenza A) had serious consequences. My mother-in-law experienced severe nausea, vomiting, dizziness, and difficulty walking due to low oxygen levels in her blood. We had to rush her to the hospital, where she was tested, confirmed to have Influenza A, admitted, and treated appropriately. The doctor at the hospital advised us to immediately stop taking all the medication prescribed by this clinic.
While I understand that not all clinics stock Influenza test kits or antiviral medications, this does not justify prescribing incorrect treatments based solely on convenience or availability. Despite being informed of our confirmed Influenza A case, the doctor proceeded with an inappropriate course of treatment, which only worsened the situation. It would have been far more responsible to recommend that we first obtain a test kit before prescribing any medication.

reviews.name: Rui Yee
reviews.text: I had an extremely poor experience with punctuality. My appointment was scheduled for 12:30 PM, and despite the clinic itself stressing the need for a strict appointment, the treatment was delayed by 40 minutes. I waited until 1:10 PM and ultimately had to leave without receiving any treatment at all. Be cautious if you have a tight timeline. Note that another patient who has got the same appointment and came in latter than me got to enter first
reviews.responseFromOwnerText:
Dear Rui Yee,

We sincerely apologise for the delay and the inconvenience you experienced during your visit. We completely understand how valuable your time is and are truly sorry that your appointment did not start as scheduled.

Occasionally, unforeseen circumstances during earlier treatments may cause delays, but we always strive to communicate and minimise any waiting time. We regret that this was not your experience.

We would appreciate the opportunity to make things right ‚Äî please contact us directly at greatsmiledental5@gmail.com so we can personally assist you and ensure a smoother visit in the future.

Thank you for your feedback ‚Äî it helps us improve our service and patient experience.

reviews.name: Candy Kun
reviews.text:
Assalamualaikum, and first of all congratulations to me!
After 7 long years of wearing braces with this clinic, I‚Äôm finally free. It‚Äôs been a journey , not a short one, but a meaningful one. Thank you, Dr. Kasma, for your service throughout my braces treatment.

Please be more professional next time. Focus on your job. I work too, and I need money just like everyone else. We all do. But the way you handle patients is far from what I expected. I hope you can improves well for your other patients future.

Thank you for your service over the past 7 years, Klinik Dr. Kasma.
reviews.responseFromOwnerText:
Waalaikumussalam. Thank you for your feedback and for being with Klinik Dr. Kasma for 6 years. We value your journey with us, but we must address some serious misunderstandings raised in your review.

We sincerely apologise for the delay and the miscommunication caused by our DSA‚Äôs mistake. The refund process for overpayment follows a standard 1‚Äì2 month policy that applies to all patients, ensuring every transaction is properly verified and documented for financial accuracy. The option to use the credit for future treatment was offered purely as a courtesy not as a refusal to refund. We take full responsibility for the situation and assure you that your refund is valid, actively being processed, and never treated as profit.

For clarification, throughout these 7 years, our clinic has never offered free scaling after braces removal. Scaling is only included before braces placement. During your visit, our doctor did ask and confirm before proceeding with the scaling, as this treatment requires payment. Both the doctor and DSA heard your confirmation before proceeding ‚Äî we would never perform a procedure simply to gain extra profit.

Regarding your scaling experience, we‚Äôre truly sorry you felt discomfort. However, our dental equipment and systems are regularly maintained, upgraded, and meet clinical standards for hygiene and patient safety. Our DSA team will undergo retraining to improve communication and patient care.

We understand your comments may have come from frustration. but the accusation that we treat patient money merely for profit is a serious and unfair claim. We uphold professionalism and honesty in every transaction ‚Äî values we will never compromise.

We truly appreciate your feedback, but it‚Äôs disheartening to see that after 6 years of care and service, one single mistake on one day has overshadowed all the effort and trust built over time. We have always treated you with respect and professionalism, and we will continue to do so with every patient who walks through our doors.

Masa prosedur, doktor sgt berhati2 dan selalu tanya anak okay ke tak. Nurse pun banyak bantu, lembut je cara dia tenangkan anak. Lepas habis, doktor bagi MC dan ubat siap terangkan satu-satu cara makan ubat dan penjagaan lepas cabut gigi. Bayaran pun mudah, staf kaunter explain dengan jelas dan sgt sopan.

Beberapa hari tu ada bengkak sikit tapi makin menyusut dan sembuh. Lepas seminggu datang semula untuk cabut benang, proses pun cepat dan tak sakit. Alhamdulillah luka sembuh cantik. reviews.textTranslated:
My son had his MOS done here. When he came, he was really nervous, his hands were coldüòÇ But the doctor and nurse treated him calmly, even joking around to make him feel relaxed. We just walked in at that time, but the staff still accepted even though the MOS procedure took a while. From the consultation, x-ray to entering the treatment room, everything was smooth

During the procedure, the doctor was very careful and always asked if the child was okay. The nurse was also very helpful, her way of calming the child was gentle. After the procedure, the doctor gave him MC and medicine and explained each and every way to take the medicine and care after the tooth extraction. Payment was easy, the counter staff explained clearly and very politely.

There was a little swelling for a few days but it was shrinking and healing. After a week, he came back to remove the stitches, the process was quick and painless. Alhamdulillah, the wound healed beautifully. I am really satisfied with the service from the doctor, nurse to the counter staff. This clinic is the best and I highly recommend it if you want to do MOS without stress ü•∞

reviews.name: ROHANA BINTI YA'ACUB
reviews.text:
Buat closegap, yg peliknya pakai kertas pasir gosok tarik gg kuat2, dgn grinder kecil tu, tujuan nk paksa gigi tu gap lg besar ke snng utk tampal? Tak tau plak kene asah gg tu bg buka. Masa call kata ikut 1 gigi 80. Sampai sn buat scalling sekali bayar nk dekat 500. Lain kali bgtau customer siap2. Jgn main caj je. Customer berhak tau sebelum buat. Kesan asah gigi tu kuat gila tarik, sampai skrg dh nk masuk 3bulan gigi dh rasa tak sedap langsung. Sengal aje. Sengal, kebas, ngilu kadang rs mcm nk tecabut gigi ni. Mau taknya kuat sgt dipaksa2 gigi tu utk bergerak. Layanan sombong plak tu. Waranty sebulan lpstu sekali je. Terus malas nk pergi. Kerja tak ikhlas. Dh ambil duit org bg la servis ada masalah utk dtg tgk. Tau ambil duit, nk bg guarantee pn takut2. 2star utk gigi yg ditampal. Walau x puas hati. Byk sgt grind smpai gg kasar & ngilu smpai skrg.gg pun ada tajam dan tak licin.ntahla menyesal rasa buat sini. Scalling aje puas hati. Bersih.

Menjawab jawapan 3/11/25.
Ok mgkin sy ingat lupa, tapi sy tak ckp 500 sy kata nk dekat. takde beza pun 300-500 jika nk dibandingkan dengan harga yg diiklankan. Kata 80/unit. Dh smpai sn 100/unit. Lain kali kalau nk advised patient buat tu buat ni, bgtau brp harga extra. Kalau tiba2 kena caj 300 lebih tak ke teperanjat customer. Dan lg 1, awak mesej bila yg tak respon? Baru beberapa harini selepas org dh buat review? Sy komplen seminggu selepas buat, respon acuh tak acuh. Ms buat tak ckp waranti sekali sebulan bila followup tegak aje ckp sekali je.pdhal tgk problem pn belum lagi. Mmg dh tak berminat la.
reviews.textTranslated:
To do closegap, the strange thing is to use sandpaper to rub and pull the teeth hard, with that small grinder, is the purpose to force the gap even bigger to paste? I don't know if the teeth need to be sharpened to open. When I called, they said it would be 80 for 1 tooth. Until I did the scaling once, I paid close to 500. Next time, tell the customer when it's done. Don't just charge. The customer has the right to know before doing it. The effect of sharpening the teeth is crazy strong and pulling, until now, it's been almost 3 months, the teeth don't feel good at all. Just sore. Sore, numb, sometimes it hurts like I want to pull out this tooth. I don't want to force the teeth to move. The arrogant service. The warranty is only once a month. I'm too lazy to go. The work is not sincere. They take money from people who give services, there are problems to come and see. They take money, but they are afraid to give a guarantee. 2 stars for the teeth that are pasted. Even though they are not satisfied. Grinded a lot to the point of being rough & sore now. The blades are sharp and not smooth. I regret doing it here. Just a quick call, I'm satisfied. Clean.

Answered 3/11/25.
Ok, maybe I forgot, but I didn't mention 500, I said it was close. There's no difference, 300-500 if you compare it to the advertised price. It said 80/unit. It's already 100/unit. Next time if you want to advise a patient to do this, tell them how much the extra cost is. If you suddenly get charged 300 more, won't the customer be shocked. And 1 more, when did you message them and they didn't respond? Just a few days after people made reviews? I complained a week after doing it, the response was indifferent. Ms. doesn't mention the warranty once a month when the follow-up is up, just mention it once. I haven't seen the problem yet. I'm really not interested.
reviews.responseFromOwnerText:
Salam hai Puan Rohana. trima kasih dah buat rawatan di klinik pergigian batrisya dan maaf atas kekurangan .Kami cuba hubungi puan tapi tiada balasan.
 1) berkaitan dengan grinder atau kertas pasir yang puan maksudkan memang antara perlalatan gigi yang kita gunakan untuk buat tampalan, tujuan nya adalah untuk mengurangkan rasa tajam dan kasar pada gigi. 
2) kalau gigi puan masih ada masalah selepas rawatan, dr boleh perbaiki. jika puan datang dalam tempoh sebulan rawatan tidak akan dikenakan charge.
3) berkaitan dengan harga, kami dah check harga rawatan puan dalam sistem kami. total harga rawatan untuk 2 unit close gap + scaling + consultation adalah rm310 dah bukan rm500 seperti yang puan maklumkan.

-scaling rm90 (promosi)
-consultation rm20
-closegap 1 unit rm100 x2 =rm200
TOTAL  RAWATAN RM310

reviews.name: May Lin Haw
reviews.text:
On 10 October 2025, I brought my mom‚Äôs denture to look for a dentist who could patch a tooth that had detached from it. I visited two clinics, but both were permanently closed. I searched on Google Maps and found C.V. Cheah Dental Surgery at Jalan Bendahara.
My mom was ill and frail. She was already on a soft and liquid diet, and without her denture, she could only consume liquids. I wanted her to be able to enjoy soft foods like tofu and porridge again.
Mr. Cheah was a lifesaver. When I arrived at his clinic, the door was closed. I called him, and he kindly opened the door and agreed to mend the denture. He did it professionally, completing the repair within 15 minutes. I was so relieved and grateful. It was a Friday. If I hadn‚Äôt found a dentist to repair the denture, my mom might not have been able to chew her food and had to rely solely on a liquid diet for another week, as I was to travel back to Selangor that Sunday and wouldn‚Äôt return to Melaka until the following Friday.
I truly appreciated Mr. Cheah‚Äôs help in patching the broken tooth. Thanks to him, my mom was able to eat‚Äîthough only a little‚Äîfor those few days before she passed away on 17 October.
reviews.responseFromOwnerText: We are saddened to hear the demise of your mother, and wish you great comfort from a God who is the greatest comforter for you and family. We are also glad to be part of helping your mother eat for those last few days before her passing. May the God who sees be with you all.

reviews.name: T X
reviews.text:
I first visited this dentist for a check-up and to inquire about getting braces because my mom made an appointment for me on 28/8/2024. During that visit, I asked the dentist if I needed any fillings. The dentist assured me that everything looked fine according to the scan, and there were no fillings required.

However, on the following day, 29/8/2024, I received a message stating that I did, in fact, need fillings. I was confused because before leaving the clinic, I specifically asked if I needed any, and the dentist had confidently said no (this was the first instance of unprofessionalism).

I returned to the dentist on 2/9/2024 to get the fillings done and to proceed with braces. After my first appointment, I was given the option of either Invisalign or metal braces. I chose metal braces. After completing the fillings, the dentist placed 8 rubber bands between my teeth, explaining that this was to create gaps. I was told the bands needed to stay for at least a week. Unfortunately, I experienced significant discomfort throughout that week, as my teeth became weak and chewing was painful.

On 5/9/2024, I texted the clinic to ask if I could come in earlier because the pain was getting worse. I was then told (the second instance of unprofessional treatment) that braces were no longer recommended at this time because I needed a root canal first. I was also informed that it typically takes 3-6 months after a root canal before braces can be done. This meant that during my previous visit, the dentist had placed the rubber bands in my mouth for no valid reason, causing me unnecessary pain.

I was advised to return to the clinic for a root canal treatment on 7/9/2024, after nearly a week of avoidable discomfort. During this visit, the dentist said anesthetic wasn‚Äôt necessary because the tooth was dead, so there wouldn‚Äôt be any pain. However, during my follow-up visit on 13/9/2024, the dentist planned to place a rubber dam before starting the root canal. She explained that anesthetic was necessary because the process might cause pain. However, after administering the anesthetic, the dentist made two unsuccessful attempts to attach the rubber dam and then decided to proceed with the root canal without it.

This left me questioning why the anesthetic was administered if the procedure could be done without the rubber dam. This was the third instance of unprofessional treatment.

Despite the unprofessional treatment from the dentist, I would like to acknowledge that the front desk staff has been very helpful and friendly throughout my visits. Their assistance made the scheduling and follow-ups smoother and more pleasant, which I truly appreciated.

Overall, though, I am deeply dissatisfied with the dental service, as it caused me unnecessary discomfort and confusion. I feel that the treatment provided was unprofessional at multiple stages.

reviews.name: Nurul Asyiqin
reviews.text: I had a truly great experience with BDB throughout my braces treatment. From the very first consultation, the service was consistently professional, friendly, and efficient. The staff were always warm and welcoming, making me feel comfortable every time I walked in. They were also very organized with appointments and always respectful of my time, which I appreciated. The Dr was exceptional highly skilled, patient, and informative. They took the time to explain each step of the process and made sure I was comfortable and confident in the treatment plan. I always felt like I was in good hands, and the results speak for themselves. The clinic itself was clean, modern, and calming, which really helped ease any anxiety I had about dental visits. The equipment was up to date, and everything was handled with a high level of professionalism and care. Overall, I highly recommend BDB to anyone considering orthodontic treatment. The service, the doctor, and the entire environment exceeded my expectations.

reviews.text:
Update Sep‚Äô24:

Was rather disappointed with the recent visit to Tan Dental. Was having dull persistent toothache and decided to visit the dental clinic, suspected my molar tooth crack as it was getting painful even when I‚Äôm drinking or gargling. Made an appointment with Dr Ong for consultation. He did an X-ray, told me no decay and it would be a waste to go ahead with extraction. He then suggested filling and I agreed to monitor again as it could be due to tooth sensitivity as well. There‚Äôs no mention of cracked tooth and he went ahead to perform the  filling and scaling for me. Everything was fine for the next 2 days (although I can still feel slight ache but decided to ignore it as I thought it might go away soon). I had terrible toothache again on the third day, even taking painkiller is no longer effective anymore. I visited another dental for check up and the doctor was able to identified the crack even before the x ray! He showed me the cracked on the molar tooth after extraction.
I just couldn‚Äôt accept the blunder/misjudgment by Dr Ong this time round ‚Ä¶.

reviews.name: Anis Arlisha
reviews.text:
I have visited this clinic thrice for two different treatments and have had extremely poor experiences with two different doctors. I strongly advise caution to anyone considering this clinic.

1. First Treatment: Whitening (with Chinese Doctor)
My first appointment was for a whitening treatment. While I was generally accepting, the procedure was done so aggressively that my gums developed a wound and felt extreme stinging. A professional should be able to perform this common procedure without causing injury (did my whitening treatment at other clinic before - not first timer)

2. Second Treatment: Scaling and Black Metal Filling Change (with Indian Doctor)
I returned for a scaling treatment, but also asked if my old black metal filling could be changed to a new white composite filling. The Indian doctor immediately said "can" without any consultation about potential risks, consequences, or the suitability of the tooth for the change. During the filling procedure, the doctor was extremely hesitant and unprofessional. She asked me more than 10 times if the filling was "okay" and in same flat with the other teeth. As a doctor, I expect them to use their own professional judgment and instruments to determine the correct bite and contour, not rely repeatedly on the patient. This made me feel she was unexperienced and unsure of how to properly trim and contour the filing.

3. The Consequences and Third Visit (with Chinese Doctor)
A few days after the filling change, I could not eat or chew using that tooth due to pain and discomfort, indicating the filling was not done correctly. I went back for a check-up. The Chinese doctor examined the tooth and said that the tooth "might be cracked" because of the changing from metal to the white filing. The permanent solution is by doing a crown. Haha went there with a NO PROBLEM tooth condition and the result that I received? MAJOR PROBLEM !!!

This clinic seems to have unexperienced doctors who perform rushed, inadequate work that ultimately creates more problems, leading to further, more costly treatments and wasting my time

ownerUpdates.text:
Dental Scaling at Gentle Dental Surgery Kota Kinabalu‚Äôs Gentle Approach to Healthier Smiles

At Gentle Dental Surgery, located in the heart of Kota Kinabalu, Sabah, we believe that a confident smile begins with a healthy mouth. One of the most important preventive dental treatments we provide is professional dental scaling and polishing. This essential procedure removes plaque, tartar, and surface stains that daily brushing and flossing alone cannot fully eliminate.

Whether you visit us for your routine 6-month check-up or to address gum health concerns, our dental team ensures your experience is gentle, thorough, and comfortable. By combining modern technology with a personalised approach, we help you maintain fresh breath, healthy gums, and a cleaner, brighter smile.

Understanding Dental Scaling

Dental scaling is a professional cleaning procedure performed by a dentist or dental hygienist to remove harmful deposits from your teeth. These deposits include:

Plaque ‚Äì a soft, sticky film of bacteria that constantly forms on teeth.

Tartar (Calculus) ‚Äì hardened plaque that cannot be removed by normal brushing.

Plaque and tartar tend to accumulate in hard-to-reach areas, such as between teeth and along the gumline. If left untreated, they can cause gum inflammation, bleeding, and eventually gum disease. Scaling removes these deposits, reducing bacterial growth and promoting gum healing.

Zoom Teeth Whitening :  A Brighter Smile in Just One Visit
At Gentle Dental Surgery, we believe that your smile should reflect your confidence. If you're looking for an effective, safe, and fast way to brighten your teeth, Zoom Teeth Whitening might be the perfect solution. Zoom whitening is one of the most popular professional teeth whitening systems used globally, offering noticeable results in just a single dental visit.

Why Choose Zoom Whitening at Gentle Dental Surgery?
We offer in-clinic Zoom whitening at our modern dental facility in Kota Kinabalu, performed by experienced dental professionals in a safe, comfortable environment. Our priority is not just a whiter smile but a healthier, more confident you.

Are you bothered by a gap between your front teeth? At Gentle Dental Surgery, we offer a safe, quick, and effective solution, midline diastema closure using aesthetic composite filling. This minimally invasive treatment is designed to close gaps between teeth, especially the front two, for a more natural, symmetrical, and confident smile.

Using high-quality tooth-coloured composite resin, our dentists skillfully sculpt and bond the material to the teeth, seamlessly blending it with your natural enamel. Whether your diastema is due to genetics, habits, or spacing issues, we customise the treatment to suit your unique smile and facial profile. Our focus is not just on closing the gap but doing so aesthetically, ensuring harmony with your overall dentition.

reviews.textTranslated: I had a very, very bad experience having root canal treatment (root extraction) with Dr. Ng. My tooth suddenly started hurting unbearably, so I rushed here for treatment. Dr. Ng said that I needed root canal treatment. I experienced two sharp pains during the procedure and raised my hand to signal for help. After the procedure, Dr. Ng said I could eat directly, but even though the anesthesia hadn't worn off, I still felt pain. She only gave me painkillers, and I thought I should eat first and then take the medication. About 40 minutes after the procedure, I only ate a few bites of a flour cake. As the anesthesia gradually wore off, my tooth started hurting more and more, even more than before the procedure. I had only lightly bitten into the flour cake and hadn't even eaten any of the toppings. The pain was even worse than before the root canal treatment. Half of my face gradually became numb, and one eye started to feel uncomfortable. So I called to inquire, but the dental assistant answered. Dr. Ng was busy, and the assistant kept telling me to take painkillers for a week. I felt this was unreasonable, especially since my face was starting to feel numb and the pain was worse than before the procedure. So I went back to the clinic to see Dr. Ng. However, after listening to my situation, Dr. Ng also told me to take painkillers and showed no intention of examining me. The problem is, before the procedure, she said there wouldn't be any pain, just some discomfort. But after the procedure, the pain didn't decrease but increased significantly, and with the facial numbness, she kept telling me to take painkillers. When I asked what would happen if I took painkillers for several days and the pain persisted, she said she would give me a refund and then cancel the procedure. Is this the attitude a doctor should have? She doesn't examine or address the problem, just offers a refund and refuses to do it. Afterwards, I took painkillers, but they were completely ineffective. I was in pain all night, and the next day I went to another clinic to finally get rid of the pain.

I had both scaling and wisdom tooth extraction done at Artius Famosa Dental Clinic, and I‚Äôm extremely satisfied with the experience!

Dr. Kan was very thorough and made sure every single tooth was properly cleaned during scaling. He even cleaned the subgingival area, which other dentist I visited before didn‚Äôt do. Although the process was a little painful (probably because I had a lot of tartar üòÖ), it was totally worth it. After the treatment, the redness and swelling in my gums improved significantly, and I no longer experienced bleeding when brushing. üòä

A week later, I had my impacted wisdom tooth surgically removed. Dr. Kan was incredibly skilled ‚Äì I barely felt any pain during the procedure, not even when the anesthesia was injected! The only scary part was the sound of the equipment üòÇ But Dr. Kan patiently removed the tooth in small pieces rather than using force or aggressive tools. I followed the post-op instructions closely, and I had no swelling or pain at all afterward!

Dr. Kan is very professional, gentle, and empathetic. He always takes the time to explain everything clearly and patiently. He‚Äôs very considerate during treatments too ‚Äì whenever I felt uncomfortable, he would pause for a moment to let me rest. The dental assistant, and the staff Isya, are also super friendly and kind. The clinic environment is clean, peaceful, and comfortable.

Thanks to Artius Famosa Dental Clinic and Dr. Kan, I'm no longer afraid of visiting dentists and have better oral health now! Highly recommend! üíØü¶∑‚ú®

reviews.text:

reviews.name: Jac T
reviews.text:
This review comes very late but it‚Äôs something that parents should be aware of, on the importance of choosing and communicating with the right dentist for your kids.
Growing up, I visited Dr Ho as a child to have dental routine check ups, scaling and filling as treatments. As one of the more popular private practices in the town in the late 90s and early 2000, it‚Äôs considered a luxury to visit as parents want our teeth to be better taken care of, rather than relying on government funded practice as more time can be spent to attend to the patient in the private.

Yet, Dr Ho failed to identify the possibility of ankylosed tooth at the age of 6-9 years old and underbite issue that both warrant a referral to seek early treatment. None of this was communicated to parents back then and i see such as a huge failure as a primary dentist and wondered on her capability as a dentist. As such, this impacted the life of the patient with misaligned bite that had been left too late to be corrected but left with full orthognathic surgery option, implant, and orthodonticx  It‚Äôs not just aesthetic issue alone, but also this was also causing other health issues for eg airway and sinus and TMJ being the essentials, and list goes on.

I have not visited this practice since I understood the context as a young adult, thus my personal record will not be recent enough to reflect on their patient record, and given that  I have a different name on the register. Although it‚Äôs unfair to review this clinic as a zero star (if I could give a zero) for other good dentists that might be out here, I want to bring it to her attention of her failure in her dentist career since I noticed she also had a cert in implantology. Wonder how the expansion of the clinic happens with her being the founder/cofounder and being this unknowledgeable. I am not the only patient who suffered from this negligence of hers, two more people I personally know had issues not referred as a kid for treatment but not to the bad extent of mine.

So choose your treating dentist appropriately, as early intervention in kids that require referral and treatment is crucial! All the golden time for intervention and treatment should not be missed as the gums also recess as you age.
